Description: I am a collector and player. I only play acoustic nowadays so I've decided to sell this beauty. She has not been played much and has spent most of her life in her case. The only flaw in this guitar is a small rash on the back just below the neck plate (pictured with pick). Otherwise she is flawless and plays very nicely. No fret wear and no pick marks. Included with the guitar:-"Vintage custom" tweed case with two lock keys-Three sets Ernie Ball 10-46 "Regular Slinky" nickel strings-Two strap locks-Tremolo arm-Two Allen keys(saddle/neck adjustment)-Fender polishing cloth-Various literature and manuals "The 60th Anniversary Strat Guitar This commemorative model is available in 2014 only Fender's 60th Anniversary Commemorative Stratocaster guitar is a beautifully crafted U.S.-made instrument that celebrates six decades of the world's greatest electric guitar. Available in 2014 only, features fine appointments such as an ash body, Fender Custom Shop Custom '54 pickups, a compound-radius fingerboard, gold hardware, custom-engraved neck plate and headstock ingot, beautiful Two-color Sunburst finish, and much more. A true gem of an instrument created to commemorate the stratocaster guitar's diamond anniversary." Would like to see her go to a good home. Please feel free to contact me with any questions. Thanks for looking
Title: Fender 60th Anniversary Commemorative Stratocaster
